text.section:
A person may not:
destroy, damage, cut, tamper with, install, tap, remove, displace, or connect with a wire, conduit, apparatus, or other equipment of a cable television company with the intent to receive cable television services without payment;
prevent, obstruct, or delay the sending, conveyance, distribution, or receiving of programming material transmitted by a cable television company;
with the intent to deprive a person of lawful compensation, receive, attempt to receive, or assist another to receive:
cable television service by trick, use of a decoder, or other fraudulent means; or
satellite cable programming that is:
offered for sale in the person's area through an unauthorized marketing system; or
received by decoding encrypted satellite cable programming;
without authority from the cable television company, connect with a cable, wire, component, or other device used to distribute cable television service;
alter:
a device installed with the authorization of a cable television company to intercept or receive a program or service carried by the company; or
equipment capable of decoding encrypted satellite cable programming to intercept or receive satellite cable programming; or
sell, rent, or offer for sale or rent a device or a plan for a device knowing that the recipient intends to use the device or to plan to do an act prohibited by this section.
